40 2021-01-03 balance disorder, vertigo, dizziness I received the vaccine 30 min. prior to starting my shift as a Nurse in the ED. About 1 hour after r... Read more
Close
I received the vaccine 30 min. prior to starting my shift as a Nurse in the ED. About 1 hour after receiving the shot while standing I felt off balance and began to have a vertigo like dizziness. I sat down and tried to drink some water but began spitting the water back up and dry heaving after trying to drink. I did not feel nauseous if I was not drinking. I did feel the sensation of a slight lump in my throat. I did not have any shortness of breath, tachycardia, rash or fever. I did not want to check in as a patient so I called my wife to come and pick me up from work. Before I left I had the pharmacy send me some Pepcid and Benadryl and I took 25mg of Benadryl and 20mg of Pepcid before leaving. I left work around 1400 and now at 1500 I am able to drink fluids. The slight lump in my throat seems to have improved. I still feel a little dizzy and off balance.

40 2021-01-10 gait disturbance, dizziness After about 15 minutes, I began to feel lightheaded and experience a tingling in my arms/hands. I'd ... Read more
Close
After about 15 minutes, I began to feel lightheaded and experience a tingling in my arms/hands. I'd guess it was related to the nerves in the arms, because it specifically affected my pinky and ring fingers on both hands. I was also unsteady on my feet, but did not lose consciousness. The lightheadedness and tingling continued off and on for most of the day. The tingling appeared to go away the next day, but I still experienced periodic (though rare) feelings of lightheadedness. Perhaps 2-3 time the next day (Saturday) and experienced maybe 1-2 times the following day (Sunday). I did not take Adderall on the weekend. On Monday, I did take Adderall and returned to work, where I experience some tingling again and longer bouts of lightheadedness. Again, I have not lost consciousness.

Patient received the Maderna Covid-19 vaccine. Was sitting in observation for 10 minutes post vaccine and got up to "make a call." I was called to the conference room at 0815. Caregivers heard a loud noise and found patient on the ground in the hallway right outside the observation room. Patient states "I got dizzy and started getting tunnel vision" also states that this happens at times with needles/ blood draws since he was a kid. Patient set up on his own, denies head/neck pain. Denies any injury. Stood on his own and guided into observation for more time- set in chair. 0832 checked with patient , still denies injury, denies anymore dizziness. Encouraged him to go to the ED to get checked out. Patient denies head/neck pain or any S/S at this time. Declines ED. 0847- Patient denies dizziness, s/s and declines going to ED. Walked out, gait steady.

Sore shoulder started after a couple of hours and was moderate by evening. A general unusual feeling started within a couple hours of the shot. By 7pm I started to experience chills and joint fatigue in legs (knees, toes). Chills became severe and a low grade fever of 100.6 developed. Chills lasted about 1.5hrs. Fever broke overnight. By morning all previous issues were resolved and the only issue was a problem with equilibrium and balance (and sore shoulder) It was a general feeling similar to drunkenness. This issue persisted throughout the day and by evening I was experiencing mild vertigo when I closed my eyes. I went to bed feeling somewhat improved relative to all the symptoms but woke having experienced a cold sweat. My shirt was completely soaked. I noted several less significant sweating issues throughout this day with no other side effects. This was the final day with notable symptoms. At the time of this report I have minor shoulder pain as the only symptom that persisted throughout. The equilibrium symptoms were severe enough that I missed a day of work.

40 2021-02-25 dizziness Within one minute of receiving vaccine, the patient became pale, stated that he felt dizzy and faint... Read more
Close
Within one minute of receiving vaccine, the patient became pale, stated that he felt dizzy and fainted. Patient regained consciousness within one minute. Upon regaining consciousness, patient reported feeling lightheaded and dizzy but was oriented to person, place and time. Skin was warm and dry but pale in color. After regaining consciousness, patient also stated that he has a history of fainting 5-6 years ago after receiving an influenza vaccination. (During screening questions, patient denied having any reactions to vaccines in the past) Patient independently moved from a chair to a laying down position on a cot and expressed an improvement in how he was feeling. Vital signs taken after event as recorded below. When asked patient stated that he does recall times when he thinks he may have been hypoglycemic in the past. Patient also states that he has been very nervous about receiving injections throughout his life. EMS called and assessed patient at the vaccination clinic site. Patient drank a 10 oz bottle of orange juice prior to EMS arriving and when EMS staff obtained his blood sugar the result was 97. EMS stated that patient was stable and all vital signs were stable. Patients skin color improved to pink. Patients wife was called by patient and she provided transportation home for patient. Prior to leaving the vaccination clinic, patient was walking around for several minutes and denied any feelings of being lightheaded or dizzy. VITALS SIGNS: 5:06pm: Heart rate: 50, Oxygen Saturation: 99% on room air 5:15 pm: Blood pressure: 100/78 ; Heart rate: 50; oxygen saturation 99% on room air. 5:20pm: Blood pressure 98/76 Heart rate:52; oxygen saturation 96% on room air. 5:34 pm: Blood pressure 92/68 Heart rate: 53 oxygen saturation 97% on room air. Vital signs taken by EMS staff were not recorded by public health nursing staff.

Fever CHILLS, MUSCLE AND JOINT PAIN, STIFFNESS IN JPOINTS OF LEGS AND HANDS Narrative: FEVER AND MUSCLE PAIN RESPONDED TO ACETAMINOPHEN AND IBUPROFEN SX LASTED SLIGHTLY OVER A DAY AND A HALF
40 2021-03-16 dizziness It has been 6 weeks since my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine for Covid-19. For the first 3-4 days I ... Read more
Close
It has been 6 weeks since my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccine for Covid-19. For the first 3-4 days I had the usual moderate flu-like symptoms: dizziness, headaches, fatigue, chills, soreness at vaccine siteetc. Days 5-7 I seemed to gradually improve. On day 8 all of the symptoms returned with greater severity: this time I had a fever, the chills were much more intense, the headaches were excruciating, body and joint aches all over the place--I couldn't sleep or focus on anything cognitively taxing. Interestingly, my brother, who was vaccinated just after me, also had more severe side effects beginning on day 8 post 2nd dose. He improved after 3-4 days, but my recovery has been much much lengthier. By day 14 I was still feeling very ill, though the fever did subside. Sometime in the third week the pain in my arm at the vaccination site returned, then became intermittent, and still bothers me from time to time. I also started getting muscle spasms in the same exact locations that sent me to the ER after my probably bout with Covid in the spring of 2020. Thankfully these lasted only a week or so, though I began feeling muscle soreness in different parts of my body, ever changing. By the 4th week I was slightly better and down to 4 main symptoms: chills (by far the worst of the symptoms--to the point at which my skin would feel like it was being frostbitten by dry ice every time I changed sweaty clothes), occasional splitting headaches, and muscle soreness that included both the injection site on my arm and other areas. I had other symptoms as well, fatigue and brain fog, etc, but these were present before the vaccination, though not as severe.

At 0908 HR 106, slightly lightheaded, rapid response arrived and transferred patient to ER at 0913 by wheelchair. Patient was alert and oriented.

Stroke; Gotten very sick from vaccine; Tachycardia; Blood pressure issues; Dizziniess; Heart rate issues; This spontaneous case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of CEREBROVASCULAR ACCIDENT (Stroke) in a 40-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. #027L20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included COVID-19 (hospitalized for 7 days; treated with Remdesivir; long recovery) from 11-Sep-2020 to October 2020. Concurrent medical conditions included Blood pressure (ongoing issues) and Heart rate (ongoing issues). On 05-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 03-Mar-2021, the patient experienced CEREBROVASCULAR ACCIDENT (Stroke) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). On an unknown date, the patient experienced ILLNESS (Gotten very sick from vaccine), TACHYCARDIA (Tachycardia), BLOOD PRESSURE FLUCTUATION (Blood pressure issues), DIZZINESS (Dizziniess) and HEART RATE IRREGULAR (Heart rate issues). At the time of the report, CEREBROVASCULAR ACCIDENT (Stroke), ILLNESS (Gotten very sick from vaccine), TACHYCARDIA (Tachycardia), BLOOD PRESSURE FLUCTUATION (Blood pressure issues), DIZZINESS (Dizziniess) and HEART RATE IRREGULAR (Heart rate issues) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 25-Mar-2021, SARS-CoV-2 antibody test: 9.64 after one round of the vaccine. On an unknown date, SARS-CoV-2 antibody test: 220 natural antibodies after 2 months. mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was withdrawn on an unknown date. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. Patient reports that he had worked for an urgent care performing testing and contracted COVID-19 back in 11SEP2020. Patient was hospitalized for 7 days, was administered Remdesivir, and had a long recovery. Patient reports having issues regulating his blood pressure and heart rate so bad that he had almost died during that time. The recovery took up until 1st week of October and did not feel well until then. Patient reports it was advised to defer first dose of vaccination for COVID-19 for 3 months. Patient self-medicated with OTC Tylenol and Advil which did not help. Patient reports that he was hospitalized a second time around last month (03MAR2021 approximately) for experiencing a stroke. Symptoms felt like he was experiencing a mini-COVID-19 episode and was having a relapse of COVID-19. ER professional advised patient to never take the second dose of the vaccine. Patient reports taking an antibody test (after a single dose of the vaccine) for both natural and for the spike protein on 25MAR2021. Patient reports that he had gotten a 9.64 reading from just one round of the vaccine in comparison to the doctors he had worked who had received both doses of the vaccine, never gotten sick with COVID-19, and produced a 9.0 reading. Patient reports his natural antibodies after 2 months was at 220. Patient wishes to report this information to highlight that his natural antibodies were so high from the previous COVID-19 infection that when he had gotten the first round of the vaccine, he believes that his body rejected the vaccine so strongly that he presented with severe side effects from the vaccine. Patient would like to submit his information to show that he is proof that if someone previously had COVID-19, they should only need a single dose of the vaccine. In addition, patient expressed that if a patient's natural antibody is high, then a reduced dose should be provided or the vaccine should be deferred until natural antibodies reduce Most recent FOLLOW-UP information incorporated above includes: On 02-Apr-2021: Event details reported; Sender's Comments: Very limited information regarding the events has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

Close
Shoulder Injury Related to Vaccine Administration (SIRVA). The Nurse Practitioner administered the shot too high on my arm, up near the shoulder. As a result, the shot was injected in or near the bursa, causing extreme pain, limited range of motion, and potentially long term damage. I was diagnosed with Bursitis in the hospital two days later following a CT scan. It does not appear the standard "two finger width" approach was followed to ensure injection into the deltoid muscle. I am still in chronic pain. I've received tramadol, percocet, and a corticosteroid injection. I have a consultation with an orthopedic surgeon next week. My shoulder was fine prior to the administration of the second vaccine, which seems to be due to poor technique by the nurse practitioner who administered it.

Dizzy; short term memory sucks and it's frustrating; Can't see well; Fibromyalgia; bone pain; Neuropathy; Feeling aches in the body; Bells palsy-paralysis on the left side of the face/ pressure on the left side of the face and neck; headache; Ringing in the ears; Pressure in the ears; A spontaneous report was received from consumer concerning a 41-year-old, male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced pressure in ears/ear discomfort, ringing in ears/tinnitus, pressure on the left side of the face and neck which was found to be Bell's Palsy/facial paralysis, Headache, neuropathy peripheral, fibromyalgia, memory impairment, couldn't see well/visual decrease, feeling aches in the body/myalgia, and dizziness. The patient's medical history included neuropathy and fibromyalgia and past cancer. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 03 Feb 2021, the patient received the first of two doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 028L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 24FEB2021 the patient began experiencing pressure and a ringing in the ears and then started like a pressure on the left side of the face and neck. On 25FEB2021, the patient started having a headache and on 26FEB2021 the paralysis on the left side of the face began. The patient said that it worsened, couldn't eat, couldn't speak, and went to the hospital. The patient said that they had a CT Scan, and the result was that it wasn't a stroke. Vitals were taken and blood work came back normal. The conclusion was Bell's Palsy. The patient stated that they couldn't see well and were dizzy. The patient said that they were experiencing fibromyalgia and neuropathy that they had when they had cancer. The patient also mentioned that they were experiencing some bone pain and that their short term memory was not good and was frustrating. Treatment of these events were not reported. The outcome of the events, ear discomfort, tinnitus, facial paralysis, headache, neuropathy peripheral, fibromyalgia, memory impairment, visual decrease, myalgia and dizziness were considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. The patient's medical history of neuropathy, fibromyalgia and past history of cancer remains the contributing factors. Further information has been requested.

When I received my first dose of the Moderna COVID vaccine (Lot # 010M20A) my arm was extremely sore and limited range of motion. I contributed it to just being sore like the literature had sad. When I received my second dose within 20 minutes my arm was extremely sore. It got to the point where I could not lift my arm at all and had no ROM in it at all. The gave me some Toradol and Decadron IM and sent me home with Naproxen and Prednisone with orders to follow up with my PCP

43 2021-03-06 dizziness Within 48 hours of receiving the COVID vaccine, I began having extreme pressure and discomfort in my... Read more
Close
Within 48 hours of receiving the COVID vaccine, I began having extreme pressure and discomfort in my right ear. Symptoms included dizziness, fullness in the ear and hearing loss. This persisted for several days. As a first course of action, I took Tylenol and antihistamines. I saw my PCP a few days later and he misdiagnosed my condition and suggested that I continue with antihistamines and Flonase. Two weeks later my condition had improved only slightly and I became more concerned. I asked my PCP whether a short course of steroids was warranted (at the suggestion of my mom and wife, who are both health care professionals). He prescribed a "dose pack," which I started on or about Monday, Feb. 22. Later that week, I connected with an ENT who is a friend of a friend . When I told him my story and symptoms he was extremely concerned and got me an immediate appointment on Friday, Feb. 26. At that visit I was diagnosed with acute and severe Sensorineural hearing loss (SNHL) that had resulted in 92% hearing loss in my right ear. Additional symptoms continue to include fullness, tinnitus and other discomfort. None of these issues existed prior to my COVID vaccine shot. I am currently undergoing a treatment of high dose prednisone and steroid injections in my ear. I am scheduled for another visit with doctor on Friday, March 12.

Patient received Moderna COVID-19 vaccination. About 10 minutes after injection patient was not looking well. I escorted him to a private area where he continued to be light headed, pale in appearance, and communicated in short sentences. While sitting patients BP was 60/40 and pulse was thready. He was placed on the floor with legs elevated and EMS called. Lungs were clear and normal, heart tones normal as well. No sings of angioedema at any point of his episode. 3 minutes later BP increased to 80/60 with a stronger radial pulse, and a recheck again about 5 minutes later resulted in a BP of 110/72 with regular radial pulse. EMS arrived and assessed patient. He refused transfer to hospital. He was given time, water, and a small meal as he had not eaten or drank much of anything through is night shift. After about 30 minutes he was able to ambulate through the auditorium and stated he was feeling much better. We encouraged him to take the remainder of the day off but he declined and returned to work. He stated he would return if any symptoms were to reoccur or if he had any concerns. He will have his next dose of vaccine in clinic.

Received Vaccine on Friday January 15th 2021 at approximately 0715am after my Isolation and having had no symptoms for over a week. Received injection, was observed by our Physician staff for approximately 35 minutes with no adverse reactions noted at that time. Approximately 30 hours later on Saturday my left arm began to hurt and a very very strong fatigue came over me and I took a 2 and a half hour nap on the couch. I was still extremely fatigued upon waking, but my arm continued to hurt more and more up to the point it wasn't usable for anything heavy and/or strenuous at all, hurting just to use it for getting up from the couch. I was assisted to get me things like water, food and stuff. The arm pain began to radiate towards my left shoulder and eventually throughout the day the pain was spreading from my shoulder to include my left upper thorax and left rib cage. By Sunday, what had begun as left arm pain had now become stronger an approximate 5/10 pain. It started to present as atypical chest pain having the pain now fully encapsulated within my left upper chest. Felt what appeared to feel like intercostal pain and a general ache all throughout. By Monday the pain was still all throughout and assessed the situation from a cardiac standpoint and found that the pain was mostly positional and I wasn't exhibiting any cardiac symptoms such as shortness of breath, no sub-sternal pain, no jaw pain, no back pain. It hurt more as I would take a deep breath and began to move my left arm around and bringing it up from my side and did a stretch with my crooked elbow of my left arm I raised it to the ceiling and moved my thorax to my right side and found that this would make it hurt more, so I did some twisting of my thorax and abdomen and found that the pain would increase from movement, it was then that I began to think that it might be Pleuritic pain. Tuesday the 19th and Wednesday the 20th I had to call in Sick because I developed a severe muscle ache below my left calf between my calf and left ankle, as if it was in constant spasm and it affected my walking, like a Charley Horse feeling and wondered if it were the same kind of feeling that I had in my chest and I found it quite odd that all my symptoms were on the left side which is the same side I received the vaccine because my right side didn't have any muscle aches. The overall chest pain began to subside over the next couple of days, but the pleuritic pain that I described never decreased in intensity or pain level. I saw my Personal Dr yesterday January 21st 2021 at approximately 5:15pm as he was walking out of his office and we discussed my symptoms and believing that my symptoms seemed to indicate some kind of tentative diagnosis of a pleurisy issue as he had agreed that there didn't seem to be any cardiac involvement and am scheduled to see him again tomorrow Saturday January 23rd at 4pm As I write this the pain continues as before with no seeming end point and is not diminishing. I had phoned and talked yesterday afternoon and felt it best to check with my primary physician because he hadn't had any reports such as mine.

2/6/2021 The day after my second Moderna vaccine shot. Woke up at 0300 feeling like I got hit by a Mack truck. Total body aches, especially the injection site on the right shoulder, the left shoulder at the old injection site (mirror pain?, Psychosomatic?, Real?), headache, jaw ache, sensitivity to light, stiffness and soreness in all muscles and joints, lethargy, no stuffy nose or congestion, but surprisingly no nausea/vomiting, instead I was super hungry. All day this persisted. I was hungry but could only eat half portions at most. Finally, after dinner, the body aches and headache had subsided. Still super tired, still painful at the injection site. I spent most of the day wearing sweatpants and sweatshirt with the hood up either on the couch or in bed with the covers up, and no sweating. Had some chills and a mild fever that came and went. At night, while wearing only my underwear, after being asleep for only an hour or two, I woke up to extreme sweating. The sheets were soaked and we had to change them. My wife said I was dripping sweat like I had just finished running for an hour. Took a shower and went back to bed in just my underwear. Had a couple more episodes when I thought I might start the extreme sweating so I flipped the covers off for a few minutes each time so I wouldn?t overheat. It did not feel like I was overheating under the covers ? just felt like I was about to start sweating again. Weird. 2/7/2021 The second day after the vaccine shot. Feeling much better, but still lethargic. Woke up late around 1030. Had brunch. Took a shower, got dressed and had to go back to bed because of the tiredness. No more chills or fever. By the late afternoon and evening I was feeling mostly back to normal. Had a full sized, normal dinner. Slept well, in my underwear, no sweating, and no chills. 2/8/2021 The third day after the vaccine shot. Woke up feeling totally normal. Got in a good 18 mile bike ride and felt fine.

Seizure like phenomena; Breath sounds abnormal; Dizziness; Dyskinesia; Eyelid function disorder; Fall; Hyperhidrosis; Hypopnoea; Hypotonia; Muscle twitching; Pallor; Presyncope; Restless legs syndrome; Tremor; This case was received via FDA VAERS on 18-May-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 18-May-2021. This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of SEIZURE LIKE PHENOMENA (Seizure like phenomena) in a 49-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 011A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included Vagal reaction (patient stated he has experienced vagal responses to injections in the past). On 02-Mar-2021 at 5:46 PM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 02-Mar-2021, the patient experienced SEIZURE LIKE PHENOMENA (Seizure like phenomena) (seriousness criterion medically significant). 02-Mar-2021, the patient experienced BREATH SOUNDS ABNORMAL (Breath sounds abnormal), DIZZINESS (Dizziness), DYSKINESIA (Dyskinesia), EYELID FUNCTION DISORDER (Eyelid function disorder), FALL (Fall), HYPERHIDROSIS (Hyperhidrosis), HYPOPNOEA (Hypopnoea), HYPOTONIA (Hypotonia), MUSCLE TWITCHING (Muscle twitching), PALLOR (Pallor), PRESYNCOPE (Presyncope), RESTLESS LEGS SYNDROME (Restless legs syndrome) and TREMOR (Tremor). At the time of the report, SEIZURE LIKE PHENOMENA (Seizure like phenomena), BREATH SOUNDS ABNORMAL (Breath sounds abnormal), DIZZINESS (Dizziness), DYSKINESIA (Dyskinesia), EYELID FUNCTION DISORDER (Eyelid function disorder), FALL (Fall), HYPERHIDROSIS (Hyperhidrosis), HYPOPNOEA (Hypopnoea), HYPOTONIA (Hypotonia), MUSCLE TWITCHING (Muscle twitching), PALLOR (Pallor), PRESYNCOPE (Presyncope), RESTLESS LEGS SYNDROME (Restless legs syndrome) and TREMOR (Tremor) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 02-Mar-2021, Blood pressure measurement: 120/72 (normal) 120/72 mmHg. On 02-Mar-2021, Heart rate: 64 (normal) 64 beats per minute. On 02-Mar-2021, Oxygen saturation: 99 (normal) 99%. On 02-Mar-2021, Respiratory rate: 20 (normal) 20 breaths per minute. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. No concomitant medications were provided. The patient remained in the vaccination chair for 5 minutes after injection and he reported feeling well and moved to the observation chair without any problems [~10ft]. After being in the observation chair the patient stood up and took 4-5 steps toward the wall and sat down on the floor. The patient stated he felt dizzy and then became limp and slumped to the right side, his eyes remained open with dilation of pupil fixed at 2mm with no blinking noted. The patient's breathing pattern became shallow and snoring sounds were noted. The patient did not respond when spoken to nor did he respond to soft shaking of the shoulders. The patient began to demonstrate large jerky body movements similar to seizure activity. The seizure like activity continued for 3-4 minutes before the patient was able to become aware of surroundings and answer orientation questions. The patient was diaphoretic, pale, shaking of hands and arms, restlessness of lower limbs with frequent repositioning/twitching of legs. EMS (emergency medical services) arrived to find the patient regaining stability. The patient reported to EMS that he is familiar with this type of response and declined to be taken anywhere. Treatment medications were not reported. Based on current available information and the temporal association between product use and the start date of the event a causal relationship cannot be excluded. I don't think that my reaction to the vaccine is super serious but it is perhaps worth noting if others are also experiencing similar symptoms. On the second day, I did have the expected arm soreness around the injection area on my right arm. That soreness faded by Saturday morning. However, on Saturday afternoon, I began experiencing some intermittent pain in my left kidney. I have had a few (3?) kidney stones since I was approximately 35 years old so it is a pain that I recognize almost immediately. I kept my spider senses awake to see where it was going to go. About an hour later, I had intermittent "flu like" pain in my arms and legs. I had been up on a ladder painting a wall and I became a bit dizzy and decided to halt the painting project. The rest of the evening was kind of crappy. Intermittent headaches, leg pain, arm pain and left kidney pain. I took 1 Alleve tablet around 8pm. It didn't seem to do much. I took a second one about an hour later (according to the instructions you can take two for you first dose) and that seemed to do the trick! I slept like a rock and so far today, all of the pain is gone including the pain in my left kidney. I have not taken any more Alleve besides the two that I took last night. Also, as of right now (2:44pm on Sunday 3/21), no kidney stone has passed. I have been urinating into a cup to see if one comes out. I cannot 100% say that any of these symptoms are related to the vaccine. However, being a Type 1 diabetic (since 1978) and the unusual kidney pain made me go, "huh." That is why I am providing this info in the event that there are others who are experiencing similar symptoms that can be tied to the vaccine and what to expect. I feel completely fine now. Yay. :)

The following is an email the patient wrote to us describing his events: I received Moderna Covid Vaccine on January 4, 2021 and February 1, 2021 at Medical Center in On the evening of January 12, 2021, I arrived home from working as a Pharmacist following a 13 hour shift at Medical Center with no medical complaints. Black out; Bloody head; Bloody nose; Very dizzy; Could not walk; felt unusually tired for mid afternoon that day; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 55-year-old male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and felt unusually tired for midafternoon/fatigue, experienced a black out/loss of consciousness and woke up face down with a bloody nose/ epistaxis and head/head injury, was very dizzy and couldn't walk/gait inability. The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant medications included dolutegravir sodium;lamivudine, pregabalin, and modafinil for unknown indication. On 19 Feb 2021, approximately two days prior to the onset of the events the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 011M20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 21 Feb 2021, after receiving mRNA-1273, the patient felt unusually tired for midafternoon that day. The patient had suffered from chronic fatigue issues but never felt more tired than usual at that point in the day. The patient then experienced a black out and woke up face down with a bloody nose and head. The patient felt very dizzy, was not able to walk and crawled to their mattress and fell asleep. The patient managed to get himself to the Emergency room, a CT scan of the head was performed, and it was revealed that the patient had a fracture that had occurred before the vaccine and was not related to the vaccine. The doctor thought the vaccine however maybe related to the blackout or have exaggerated a concussion and have caused these delayed symptoms. No treatment information was provided. The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the events, therefore action taken with the drug in response to the events was not applicable. The outcome of the event experienced a black out was resolved at the time of this report and the outcome of the events, felt unusually tired for midafternoon, woke up face down with a bloody nose and head, was very dizzy and couldn't walk was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: Based on reporter's causality and patient's skull fracture that had occurred before the vaccine the event is assessed as unlikely related to mRNA-1273.; Sender's Comments: US-MODERNATX, INC.-MOD-2021-057947:Second Dose Case

On 15-Apr-2021, after starting mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine), the patient experienced DIZZINESS (Little dizzy). On 16-Apr-2021, the patient experienced HAEMATOCHEZIA (Blood in the stool) (seriousness criterion medically significant), DIARRHOEA (Diarrhoea), ABDOMINAL PAIN UPPER (Stomach cramping) and HEADACHE (Head ache). Event onset 2 days after second dose mRNA-1273. Event outcomes unknown. 4/30/21- Pt is a 56yo White male who presented to the Clinic for 1st Moderna vaccine via MyTurn registration. Patient answered No to all of the vaccination screening questions on MyTurn. At 1000, patient was checked in by staff. Immunization was administered approximately at 1002. Around 1007, the clinic providers were called for emergency response by CORE team member who was stationed at the observation area because this patient lost consciousness, fell down, and hit his head. NP arrived to the scene with Emergency Epinephrine pen and benadryl tablets. RN was already at scene and assessed for patient's consciousness. EMS was called by Google volunteer. Patient was seated in the chair, being monitored by the clinic and CORE team member. Pt was unresponsive and actively undergoing tonic seizure-like activity with sustained posturing of bilateral hands in decorticate "cup" position. Patient's eyes were open during entire seizure-like activity, but unresponsive to stimuli. Inflamed abrasions were noted on patient's right temporal lobe, right cheek, and bilateral lower extremities near the knees. No active bleeding was seen. At 1008, Pt regained consciousness after 10 seconds of seizure activity and began to answer RN's questions. Patient stated that he was "fine" and answered that he knew his current location "at the vaccination site." Pt was unaware that he lost consciousness, fell to the ground, and hit his head. Pt denied any active medical illnesses, hx of seizures, or reactions to prior vaccinations. Pt stated that he drove here to the appointment. Patient was given bottle of water, which he started drinking. NP measured pt with pulse oximeter, reading 98% O2 Saturation and 61bpm for heart rate. NP arrived to the scene. The medical staff RN, NP, and NP advised for patient to stay and wait for EMS out of concern for his own safety and the safety of others because he will be driving home. We informed pt that EMS has already been called and for him to stay hydrated while waiting. Pt stated "I do not want to go to the hospital" and refused EMS evaluation. I informed pt that due to sustained head injury, LOC, and seizure activity, we highly advise for patient to seek further medical evaluation. Pt refused and walked away from the observation area to his car. Adverse Reaction was reported to VAERS and CMO of the clinic.

Passing out, dry cough so bad that he would faint; Stood up to cough, passed out, and fell and his head hit the concrete; Head hit the concrete floor, hitting head on floor; Bad, dry cough; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passing out, dry cough so bad that he would faint) in a 56-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch nos. G17-C21A and G26-B21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. Concurrent medical conditions included Smoker (30+ years of smoking.) and Vapor cigarette smoker (vaping the past two years.). Concomitant products included BENZTROPINE [BENZATROPINE], FLUOXETINE, TAMSULOSIN, CLONAZEPAM, AMLODIPINE and LURASIDONE HYDROCHLORIDE (LATUDA) for an unknown indication. On 05-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 03-May-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 12-Apr-2021, the patient experienced LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passing out, dry cough so bad that he would faint) (seriousness criterion medically significant), FALL (Stood up to cough, passed out, and fell and his head hit the concrete), HEAD INJURY (Head hit the concrete floor, hitting head on floor) and COUGH (Bad, dry cough). On 12-May-2021, LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (Passing out, dry cough so bad that he would faint) and COUGH (Bad, dry cough) had resolved. At the time of the report, FALL (Stood up to cough, passed out, and fell and his head hit the concrete) and HEAD INJURY (Head hit the concrete floor, hitting head on floor) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): In April 2021, SARS-CoV-2 test: negative (Negative) Went to get tested for COVID-19 due to dry, bad cough and came back negative. The patient stated that approximately one week after the first dose, he was having a bad dry cough. The dry cough was so bad that when he was sitting on recliner he would cough so bad, he would faint and pass out. One time the patient stood up to cough, passed out, and fell and his head hit the concrete floor. He went to emergency department three times because of this cough. On 12 MAY 2021, the patient stopped experiencing coughing and passing out. The patient also stated that he has no other side effects and that his healthcare provider thinks this experience was attributed to the first vaccine. Patient was prescribed an "inhaler" from his healthcare provider to help with "lungs and stuff." The patient also has an appointment with a pulmonologist in June. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable. Head injury was due to fall and thus cannot be directly associated with mRNA-1273 use. The other events are temporarily associated with the product use and a causal relationship cannot be excluded This case was linked to MOD-2021-138832 (Patient Link).; Sender's Comments: Head injury was due to fall and thus cannot be directly associated with mRNA-1273 use. Subjective 57 y.o. male who was seen at COVID Vaccine Clinic today for his second dose of the COVID 19 vaccination. He was given the Moderna vaccination in the right deltoid muscle. During his 15 minute waiting period after the injection, the patient began to experience Right sided chest discomfort, mild shortness of breath and intermittent dizziness. He denied rash, hives, welts, difficulty breathing, difficulty swallowing, wheezing, throat tightness, hoarseness, stridor, itching, lightheadedness, dizziness, facial swelling, lip swelling and tongue swelling. This provider was notified of patient reaction and he was then assessed in the emergency area. Monitored patient for severe reaction symptoms, including but not limited to abdominal pain, blood pressure abnormality , chest pain, collapse, drooling, hypotension, increased swelling, rapid progression of symptoms, respiratory distress, skin changes, tongue swelling and vomiting. patient denies any previous cardiac history but does have Asthma. Chest discomfort did not worsen with activity and actually improved some per his report. ALLERGY REVIEW OF SYSTEMS: Patient complains of chest tightness (Right side, no radiation) and dizziness (Intermittent) Previous Reactions: None Objective Vitals Vitals: 02/05/21 1009 02/05/21 1019 BP: 136/83 130/83 Pulse: 70 62 Resp: 14 SpO2: 98% 98% Physical Exam Vitals signs reviewed. Constitutional: General: He is not in acute distress. Appearance: He is not diaphoretic. Cardiovascular: Rate and Rhythm: Normal rate. Heart sounds: Normal heart sounds. No murmur. Pulmonary: Effort: Pulmonary effort is normal. No respiratory distress. Breath sounds: Normal breath sounds. No wheezing. Neurological: Mental Status: He is alert. Assessment/Plan Treatment included: albuterol, water and Acetaminophen Follow up response to treatment: Excellent Patient discharge: Stable to go home and follow up with PCP. Differential Diagnosis: Vaccine-Related Anxiety (include misc mental health) and Local reaction (arm pain, bleeding/bruising, mechanical irritation, localized rash) Symptoms developed just prior to patient leaving, started visit at 10:05 am, self administered albuterol at 10:10am. Self administered Acetaminophen 1,000 mg at 10:24 AM, Symptoms resolved and patient discharged around 10:30 AM. History of anxiety. Showed great relief of symptoms with use of his personal Albuterol inhaler and 1,000 mg of Acetaminophen (also his own). Symptoms completely subsided prior to discharge.

Patient admitted with high grade AV block, sinus pause, and recurrent syncope. 57-year-old white male with PMH only of cigarette use who notes about 2 weeks of generalized malaise, then in the last 24 hours has had 2 syncopal episodes that were accompanied by diaphoresis only without other prodrome. He got his second dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on 5/28/21, then on the following day had been working in the barn without any dyspnea chest pain or shortness of breath but felt generally fatigued so went to take a nap. He got up to check his temperature, then "just hit the floor". Not preceded by blackout of vision, lightheadedness, chest pain, dyspnea palpitations, nausea but was accompanied by sweats. He believes he was out only briefly, and when he awoke was not confused and did not have tongue biting or loss of bladder or bowel continence. He then got up and went about his day normally, then around 2 AM awoke to let the dogs out and had an identical event, but this time hit his chin on a chain saw on the floor and suffered a laceration. He presented to ED for evaluation where his laceration was sutured. He is hemodynamically stable and afebrile. Initial labs and diagnostics are unrevealing and an EKG showed a normal sinus rhythm without acute or chronic ischemic changes. Noncontrast CT of the head and the face showed no evidence of bony damage, no intracranial bleed or large territory infarct. While in the ED, the patient had a brief bradycardic episode accompanied by diaphoresis although a dedicated strip is not available and it is unclear what his rhythm was. He did not syncopize. Hospitalist service was asked to accept for syncope evaluation. When admitting physician saw patient, he reported feeling completely well without any other issues. He does note he had about 2 weeks of malaise before all of this started and a mild decrease in his ability to work intensely, but had attributed this to cigarette smoking. Review of systems was essentially negative. He is a hobby farmer and has had a couple of tick bites this year. While admitting physician was in the room at the end of the visit, the patient had an episode of diaphoresis and went into a high-grade second-degree AV block with disappearance of atrial activity without ventricular escape and lost consciousness for about a second. No jerking or twitching observed. The episode a couple of seconds then self terminated and the patient awoke and completely recovered mentation and was in a sinus rhythm. He was diaphoretic and felt ill afterward this. He had no chest pain or dyspnea. Immediately after the episode with repeat vitals the patient's heart rate was in the 70s and a normal sinus rhythm and blood pressure is 136/80. Oxygen saturations are preserved. Not on any rate limiting agents either here in emergency department or at home. Patient found to have P-P interval prolongation with AV block and subsequent sinus arrest possibly situational in the setting of coming off of a colonoscopy and receiving second Moderna COVID-19 vaccine. A pacemaker was placed 6/1/2021 without complication and the patient was discharged in stable condition on 6/2/2021.

On 07-Apr-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. In May 2021, the patient experienced ARTHRALGIA (Diagnosed him with joint inflammation).
